WEBVTT


00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:22.940
♪Only after bloom comes fruit♪

00:00:24.350 --> 00:00:28.320
♪Who says glory must fade to the past♪

00:00:30.980 --> 00:00:36.070
♪Only through thunder
do you reach the clouds♪

00:00:37.270 --> 00:00:42.180
♪Who made you the crown of every peak♪

00:00:43.710 --> 00:00:46.990
♪I stand at the center of the stage♪

00:00:46.990 --> 00:00:50.060
♪My shadow is pinned against the wall♪

00:00:50.770 --> 00:00:55.720
♪Facing the light earns every medal♪

00:00:56.760 --> 00:00:59.940
♪Little birds,
save your needless pecking♪

00:00:59.940 --> 00:01:03.220
♪The open sky rises high♪

00:01:03.760 --> 00:01:08.890
♪When night falls,
the moon begins to shine♪

00:01:09.660 --> 00:01:12.920
♪I stand in the heart of these lands♪

00:01:12.920 --> 00:01:16.280
♪My shadow bears no crown or robe♪

00:01:16.690 --> 00:01:22.360
♪Then I know truth needs no disguise♪

00:01:22.770 --> 00:01:26.020
♪The green hills see me as I am♪

00:01:26.020 --> 00:01:29.350
♪Like dew, lightning,
and moon on the river♪

00:01:29.750 --> 00:01:33.790
♪Showing me exactly who I am♪

00:01:33.790 --> 00:01:35.040
=The Lead=

00:01:36.020 --> 00:01:37.940
=Episode 33=

00:01:40.960 --> 00:01:41.800
Feng Xiaoxiao.

00:01:45.680 --> 00:01:46.640
It really is you.

00:01:47.000 --> 00:01:47.960
What are you doing here?

00:01:49.840 --> 00:01:50.680
Just taking a walk.

00:01:51.520 --> 00:01:53.680
You walked all the way from Ningzhou?

00:01:58.560 --> 00:01:59.960
When did you start drinking?

00:02:00.880 --> 00:02:01.920
Do I even need to learn?

00:02:02.160 --> 00:02:04.520
It's easy
when you don't want to be sober.

00:02:10.880 --> 00:02:12.440
You're here for Yi Qin'e?

00:02:18.200 --> 00:02:19.520
Yi Qin'e is so lucky.

00:02:20.400 --> 00:02:21.720
She's about to play the lead.

00:02:26.000 --> 00:02:26.960
She deserves it.

00:02:32.560 --> 00:02:33.400
True.

00:02:34.320 --> 00:02:36.120
Everyone loves her wherever she goes.

00:02:36.800 --> 00:02:38.360
Back in Ningzhou,

00:02:38.720 --> 00:02:41.960
Troupe Leader Zhu, Ms. Hua,
and Mr. Gu loved her.

00:02:42.440 --> 00:02:43.920
Now, at the provincial troupe,

00:02:44.520 --> 00:02:46.360
Troupe Leader Shan, Director Feng,

00:02:47.320 --> 00:02:48.400
and you love her.

00:02:49.720 --> 00:02:50.840
Everyone loves her.

00:02:50.960 --> 00:02:52.360
You missed one.

00:02:53.560 --> 00:02:55.240
That guy named Liu.

00:02:57.520 --> 00:02:59.000
You saw Liu Hongbing?

00:02:59.640 --> 00:03:00.880
Look how curious you are.

00:03:03.680 --> 00:03:05.360
We have nothing to do with each other.

00:03:10.320 --> 00:03:11.680
When are you returning to Ningzhou?

00:03:13.680 --> 00:03:14.720
I'm not going back.

00:03:15.800 --> 00:03:17.240
I'll go south to find opportunities.

00:03:18.840 --> 00:03:21.440
Stop drinking!
Aren't you singing anymore?

00:03:21.440 --> 00:03:22.760
Don't you care about your voice?

00:03:22.960 --> 00:03:24.360
It's too late for that.

00:03:25.520 --> 00:03:26.360
Why?

00:03:28.360 --> 00:03:29.320
My voice is ruined.

00:03:33.560 --> 00:03:35.440
Don't tell Yi Qin'e I'm going south.

00:03:36.640 --> 00:03:37.640
Don't distract her.

00:06:15.360 --> 00:06:17.160
(During the fire breathing that day,)

00:06:17.720 --> 00:06:19.040
(in Yi Qin'e's mind,)

00:06:19.040 --> 00:06:21.520
(she didn't think of any techniques.)

00:06:22.120 --> 00:06:24.800
(She only thought of Feng Xiaoxiao.)

00:06:25.360 --> 00:06:27.280
(Breath by breath,)

00:06:27.640 --> 00:06:28.800
(time after time,)

00:06:29.680 --> 00:06:32.760
(the long flame she couldn't master)

00:06:32.800 --> 00:06:34.200
(finally burst out.)

00:06:34.880 --> 00:06:37.160
(Yi Qin'e suddenly understood)

00:06:38.080 --> 00:06:41.840
(why Li Hui Niang risked her soul)

00:06:42.160 --> 00:06:46.320
(by fire breathing to save Pei.)

00:06:47.560 --> 00:06:50.840
(Life and death in the play)

00:06:50.920 --> 00:06:52.600
(aren't just empty words.)

00:06:53.400 --> 00:06:54.680
(It's about tearing out)

00:06:54.680 --> 00:06:56.600
(the most painful piece of flesh)

00:06:57.160 --> 00:07:00.600
(Yunnan Baiyao, Mercurochrome)
(to sing it.)

00:07:01.280 --> 00:07:03.360
(Parting on stage is acting;)

00:07:04.160 --> 00:07:05.800
(parting off stage)

00:07:06.520 --> 00:07:07.840
(is destiny.)

00:08:11.640 --> 00:08:12.480
Take it off!

00:08:12.680 --> 00:08:13.920
Take it off, hurry!

00:08:14.200 --> 00:08:15.400
Take it off now!

00:08:15.840 --> 00:08:17.560
Hurry, take it off!

00:08:23.880 --> 00:08:24.920
Fire!

00:08:25.320 --> 00:08:26.560
Put out the fire!

00:08:26.560 --> 00:08:27.600
Fire!

00:08:27.840 --> 00:08:29.120
Hurry, put out the fire!

00:08:29.360 --> 00:08:30.600
- Fire!
- Put it out!

00:08:30.600 --> 00:08:31.750
Put out the fire!

00:08:32.300 --> 00:08:36.180
(Beishan Government Office in Chang'an)

00:08:36.200 --> 00:08:37.280
Come on, Hongbing.

00:08:37.720 --> 00:08:38.560
Have some tea.

00:08:40.260 --> 00:08:43.420
(Employee Transfer Registration Form)

00:08:43.440 --> 00:08:44.280
Hongbing,

00:08:45.040 --> 00:08:46.960
your handwriting is incredible.

00:08:47.320 --> 00:08:48.960
It's exactly like your dad's.

00:08:49.960 --> 00:08:50.800
I actually asked

00:08:50.840 --> 00:08:52.560
your dad for this calligraphy.

00:08:53.280 --> 00:08:55.120
Never forget who dug the well.

00:08:55.640 --> 00:08:56.720
This is great. Really good.

00:08:56.720 --> 00:08:57.560
Li,

00:08:58.080 --> 00:08:59.840
is the paperwork almost done?

00:09:01.280 --> 00:09:03.200
Your paperwork is all set.

00:09:03.490 --> 00:09:04.380
From now on,

00:09:04.400 --> 00:09:06.080
you'll work in the office next to mine.

00:09:07.600 --> 00:09:08.440
Just take it.

00:09:10.200 --> 00:09:12.080
Hongbing, what's all this?

00:09:12.600 --> 00:09:14.680
Your dad is my mentor.

00:09:15.280 --> 00:09:16.320
Don't do this again.

00:09:18.680 --> 00:09:19.520
Li,

00:09:20.280 --> 00:09:21.120
I have a question.

00:09:21.640 --> 00:09:24.400
Are we busy with reception work lately?

00:09:25.080 --> 00:09:25.920
Why?

00:09:26.520 --> 00:09:27.360
What's wrong?

00:09:28.680 --> 00:09:30.440
My girlfriend's taking the stage soon.

00:09:30.800 --> 00:09:32.320
I've got a lot going on at home.

00:09:32.360 --> 00:09:33.720
I get it.

00:09:35.080 --> 00:09:36.800
You don't need to clock in.

00:09:36.800 --> 00:09:38.200
Your hours are flexible.

00:09:38.640 --> 00:09:40.240
I'll assign tasks to others.

00:09:40.640 --> 00:09:42.280
If there's an important reception,

00:09:42.280 --> 00:09:43.280
I'll send you.

00:09:43.800 --> 00:09:46.520
Alright, Li. That's it, then.

00:09:46.800 --> 00:09:47.640
By the way,

00:09:47.840 --> 00:09:49.520
I need a favor from you.

00:09:50.160 --> 00:09:52.640
When is your girlfriend performing?

00:09:53.080 --> 00:09:54.960
Can you get us some tickets?

00:09:54.960 --> 00:09:57.000
Let us go check it out.

00:09:57.000 --> 00:09:58.400
It's nothing.

00:09:58.680 --> 00:09:59.840
Are 20 tickets enough?

00:10:01.360 --> 00:10:03.200
She was practicing fire breathing there.

00:10:03.200 --> 00:10:04.080
And it caught fire.

00:10:04.673 --> 00:10:06.080
That's no place for fire breathing.

00:10:06.080 --> 00:10:06.920
Yeah.

00:10:07.600 --> 00:10:08.920
Luckily, I found out early.

00:10:09.080 --> 00:10:10.120
If I were any later,

00:10:10.280 --> 00:10:12.280
this whole area would be burned.

00:10:13.108 --> 00:10:15.042
- What took you so long?
- Why are you so late?

00:10:15.053 --> 00:10:16.240
- Go look.
- How am I late?

00:10:28.640 --> 00:10:29.480
Where is she?

00:10:29.600 --> 00:10:30.600
In the hospital.

00:10:30.920 --> 00:10:31.880
Which hospital?

00:10:32.200 --> 00:10:33.040
I don't know.

00:10:35.713 --> 00:10:36.840
(Emergency Room)
She's fine.

00:10:36.860 --> 00:10:38.280
We'll observe her after the IV drip.

00:10:38.291 --> 00:10:39.400
Then you can take her home.

00:10:39.440 --> 00:10:40.800
Can she still perform on stage?

00:10:41.160 --> 00:10:42.520
That depends on her condition.

00:10:42.760 --> 00:10:44.240
It's fine as long as she's okay.

00:10:48.960 --> 00:10:49.800
How are you doing?

00:10:50.840 --> 00:10:51.760
How do you feel?

00:10:52.360 --> 00:10:54.760
Do you feel uncomfortable anywhere else?

00:10:55.720 --> 00:10:56.560
I won't perform.

00:10:57.040 --> 00:10:57.880
What?

00:10:58.360 --> 00:11:00.160
I won't be the lead in You Xi Hu.

00:11:01.600 --> 00:11:03.040
Why is that?

00:11:03.240 --> 00:11:04.080
Qin'e,

00:11:04.600 --> 00:11:05.880
are you afraid of being replaced?

00:11:06.400 --> 00:11:08.520
Listen, from the start of this project,

00:11:08.520 --> 00:11:09.960
you were chosen as the lead.

00:11:10.400 --> 00:11:11.280
The main thing is

00:11:11.560 --> 00:11:13.840
that the provincial troupe is huge.

00:11:14.000 --> 00:11:15.400
All these intermediate steps

00:11:15.400 --> 00:11:17.080
require some procedures.

00:11:20.120 --> 00:11:22.640
If you have other demands, just say so.

00:11:23.840 --> 00:11:26.160
This project is a nationwide tour.

00:11:26.240 --> 00:11:28.120
It's a major provincial project.

00:11:28.320 --> 00:11:29.600
It's required by the higher-ups.

00:11:29.600 --> 00:11:31.160
It's not your call to make.

00:11:31.360 --> 00:11:33.200
I'm not doing it.

00:11:34.160 --> 00:11:35.520
At worst, I'll go back to Ningzhou.

00:11:36.120 --> 00:11:37.040
You...

00:11:37.120 --> 00:11:38.240
Let's discuss this later.

00:11:39.720 --> 00:11:40.720
We'll talk later.

00:11:52.520 --> 00:11:53.760
Lili, have some water.

00:11:55.200 --> 00:11:56.040
Here.

00:11:56.840 --> 00:11:58.080
I got us a roast chicken.

00:11:59.760 --> 00:12:01.400
From Daokou. Your favorite.

00:12:02.400 --> 00:12:03.240
Come on.

00:12:16.120 --> 00:12:16.960
Lili.

00:12:17.520 --> 00:12:18.360
Don't worry.

00:12:20.160 --> 00:12:21.040
We're bound

00:12:21.600 --> 00:12:23.320
to make it big.

00:12:26.160 --> 00:12:27.800
Anything beats singing opera.

00:13:02.080 --> 00:13:02.920
Here.

00:13:05.680 --> 00:13:06.520
Alright.

00:13:06.600 --> 00:13:07.520
For the next few days,

00:13:07.840 --> 00:13:09.080
just stay at my place.

00:13:09.880 --> 00:13:10.920
Where will you stay, then?

00:13:11.560 --> 00:13:13.120
I can make do anywhere.

00:13:14.040 --> 00:13:14.920
Go to my place.

00:13:15.680 --> 00:13:17.200
Grab my toiletries.

00:13:17.400 --> 00:13:18.940
I'll stay here with her for a few days.

00:13:20.280 --> 00:13:21.280
I'll go right now then.

00:13:25.040 --> 00:13:26.240
What's going on?

00:13:26.240 --> 00:13:27.160
She was so close.

00:13:27.160 --> 00:13:28.280
Why drop out of the show now?

00:13:29.160 --> 00:13:31.000
I promised Laidi

00:13:31.520 --> 00:13:34.040
that if she feels wronged
and wants to quit,

00:13:34.400 --> 00:13:35.440
I won't push her.

00:13:35.960 --> 00:13:37.440
You won't even ask why?

00:13:38.320 --> 00:13:39.160
What's there to ask?

00:13:40.200 --> 00:13:42.360
She's been through so much
over the years.

00:13:42.520 --> 00:13:43.720
She's bottling it up inside.

00:13:43.720 --> 00:13:45.720
She tells no one, and I can't ask.

00:13:45.720 --> 00:13:46.880
A while back,

00:13:47.000 --> 00:13:47.960
she suffered so much

00:13:48.640 --> 00:13:50.000
and didn't even say a word.

00:13:50.360 --> 00:13:51.240
When I see that,

00:13:51.720 --> 00:13:53.400
it breaks my heart.

00:13:54.360 --> 00:13:56.680
I don't even dare to think
about some things.

00:13:57.160 --> 00:13:58.080
It's all up to her now.

00:13:58.440 --> 00:13:59.600
If it's not meant to be,

00:14:00.360 --> 00:14:01.520
we won't force it.

00:14:02.160 --> 00:14:03.880
At least she has a stable job now.

00:14:04.760 --> 00:14:05.600
That's it, then.

00:14:06.320 --> 00:14:07.760
What a surprise.

00:14:07.760 --> 00:14:08.760
You've really grown.

00:14:08.960 --> 00:14:09.800
What's wrong?

00:14:10.360 --> 00:14:11.880
Tough guys have a soft side too.

00:14:12.160 --> 00:14:14.920
I meant the old man
finally kept his word.

00:14:15.680 --> 00:14:17.040
I think you're the tough one.

00:14:17.040 --> 00:14:17.880
Go on now.

00:14:24.720 --> 00:14:25.600
What are you sewing?

00:14:25.760 --> 00:14:26.600
There's a burn hole?

00:14:27.840 --> 00:14:28.720
Let's not mend it.

00:14:28.720 --> 00:14:30.069
Tomorrow, we'll go to Luoma Market

00:14:30.080 --> 00:14:31.160
to buy some nice clothes.

00:14:31.560 --> 00:14:33.080
I can still wear it if I mend it.

00:14:33.520 --> 00:14:35.160
Things at Luoma Market are so pricey.

00:14:35.560 --> 00:14:36.400
Then, give it to me.

00:14:36.640 --> 00:14:37.560
I'll mend it for you.

00:14:37.760 --> 00:14:38.600
Careful.

00:14:42.720 --> 00:14:45.360
A little mending goes a long way.

00:14:52.560 --> 00:14:53.400
Aunt Hua,

00:14:54.960 --> 00:14:56.160
I did it.

00:14:56.640 --> 00:14:57.480
What is it?

00:15:01.200 --> 00:15:04.120
Master Gou said a Baozi needs
81 breaths of fire.

00:15:04.360 --> 00:15:05.720
I blew 82.

00:15:06.920 --> 00:15:08.360
That's a good thing.

00:15:09.080 --> 00:15:10.560
Why aren't you happy?

00:15:13.560 --> 00:15:14.800
I always thought

00:15:15.600 --> 00:15:17.840
81 breaths of fire was my path.

00:15:18.520 --> 00:15:21.400
I chased it all the way here.

00:15:22.200 --> 00:15:23.200
But

00:15:27.880 --> 00:15:29.800
I feel like I've lost my way now.

00:15:30.200 --> 00:15:31.600
I don't know where to go.

00:15:32.680 --> 00:15:34.400
How can people be like sheep,

00:15:34.400 --> 00:15:36.560
always being led and herded?

00:15:38.400 --> 00:15:39.720
You were young before.

00:15:40.120 --> 00:15:41.720
Now, you're all grown up.

00:15:42.000 --> 00:15:44.000
You have to walk your own path.

00:15:44.520 --> 00:15:47.600
Take the provincial troupe, for example.

00:15:47.960 --> 00:15:49.600
Didn't you earn that yourself?

00:15:52.560 --> 00:15:54.040
In this life,

00:15:54.200 --> 00:15:55.840
you can't always just rush forward.

00:15:56.960 --> 00:15:58.200
If you don't know where to go,

00:15:58.200 --> 00:15:59.440
just stop.

00:15:59.600 --> 00:16:00.720
Rest when you need to.

00:16:01.120 --> 00:16:02.360
What's wrong with that?

00:16:05.520 --> 00:16:06.600
Since coming to Chang'an,

00:16:06.600 --> 00:16:08.160
you haven't gone out for fun, right?

00:16:09.560 --> 00:16:10.400
Me neither.

00:16:10.560 --> 00:16:11.600
No business tomorrow.

00:16:11.600 --> 00:16:12.800
Let's go hang out.

00:16:13.400 --> 00:16:14.240
Okay.

00:16:16.680 --> 00:16:17.520
Uncle Sanyuan!

00:16:18.080 --> 00:16:19.760
Uncle Sanyuan! Something bad happened!

00:16:20.240 --> 00:16:21.440
Qin'e's house caught fire!

00:16:21.800 --> 00:16:23.080
What are you yelling about?

00:16:23.720 --> 00:16:24.560
Qin'e?

00:16:25.240 --> 00:16:26.200
Why are you here?

00:16:26.840 --> 00:16:27.840
Are you okay?

00:16:29.480 --> 00:16:30.720
You scared me to death!

00:16:30.840 --> 00:16:31.800
I went to that room.

00:16:31.800 --> 00:16:33.640
It was burned pitch black.

00:16:33.760 --> 00:16:35.422
I thought
that since it burned like that,

00:16:35.433 --> 00:16:36.960
what could have happened to you?

00:16:37.160 --> 00:16:39.040
- Keep it down.
- I was so worried!

00:16:39.840 --> 00:16:41.040
I'm just glad you're safe.

00:16:41.040 --> 00:16:41.880
What are you doing?

00:16:42.240 --> 00:16:43.680
We need to celebrate!

00:16:45.120 --> 00:16:46.080
Aunt Hua is here too.

00:16:47.000 --> 00:16:48.640
I ran so fast that I almost passed out!

00:16:48.720 --> 00:16:49.640
It's okay, Aunt Hua.

00:16:49.760 --> 00:16:51.080
Let's skip cooking tonight.

00:16:51.113 --> 00:16:52.015
I'll go buy groceries.

00:16:52.026 --> 00:16:52.793
I'll cook for us.

00:16:54.920 --> 00:16:56.800
I'm just so glad you're okay.

00:16:56.840 --> 00:16:57.680
Really.

00:16:57.880 --> 00:16:59.240
Aunt, listen.

00:16:59.240 --> 00:17:00.440
When we eat tonight,

00:17:00.440 --> 00:17:01.440
I'll make you noodles.

00:17:01.840 --> 00:17:03.400
- Okay.
- Stop yelling.

00:17:07.040 --> 00:17:08.440
This is so embarrassing.

00:17:10.400 --> 00:17:12.000
Why is he like this?

00:17:22.700 --> 00:17:25.940
(Rou Jia Mo, unique flavor)

00:18:14.420 --> 00:18:15.780
(Great films, private rooms inside)

00:18:32.010 --> 00:18:43.350
(Qinqiang Opera Bai She Zhuan)
♪West Lake is still the same♪

00:18:53.760 --> 00:18:54.600
What's wrong?

00:18:55.880 --> 00:18:57.000
Feeling bored?

00:18:58.760 --> 00:19:00.520
I've never felt like this before.

00:19:02.960 --> 00:19:04.720
A day suddenly feels so long.

00:19:06.080 --> 00:19:07.920
Why is time moving so slowly?

00:19:10.520 --> 00:19:11.560
Time flies

00:19:12.520 --> 00:19:13.520
when you're performing?

00:19:15.160 --> 00:19:16.000
Aunt Hua,

00:19:16.920 --> 00:19:18.280
are you going to talk me out of it?

00:19:21.120 --> 00:19:22.080
Can I?

00:19:23.040 --> 00:19:23.880
Go ahead.

00:19:26.080 --> 00:19:27.720
Ever since I said I'd quit performing,

00:19:27.840 --> 00:19:29.640
you and Uncle haven't said a word.

00:19:30.360 --> 00:19:32.120
It actually makes me uneasy.

00:19:33.520 --> 00:19:34.360
I won't.

00:19:36.240 --> 00:19:37.400
Your uncle said

00:19:38.160 --> 00:19:39.826
he won't try
to change your mind anymore.

00:19:40.080 --> 00:19:41.080
Neither will I.

00:19:41.760 --> 00:19:43.320
We respect your choice.

00:19:44.560 --> 00:19:46.200
Besides, you're still young.

00:19:46.360 --> 00:19:47.840
You'll have plenty of chances later.

00:19:48.600 --> 00:19:49.960
Even if you really quit,

00:19:49.960 --> 00:19:50.800
so what?

00:19:52.400 --> 00:19:53.640
In this life,

00:19:55.160 --> 00:19:57.080
as kids, we listen to our parents.

00:19:58.080 --> 00:20:00.200
As adults, we listen to our bosses.

00:20:00.960 --> 00:20:03.360
In old age, we listen to our kids.

00:20:04.360 --> 00:20:06.400
How much can we decide for ourselves?

00:20:06.880 --> 00:20:08.360
Just go do whatever you want.

00:20:10.960 --> 00:20:12.640
Besides,

00:20:13.520 --> 00:20:15.520
what's so good about being the lead?

00:20:16.360 --> 00:20:17.320
A full-length opera

00:20:18.280 --> 00:20:19.840
has 300 or 400 lines of lyrics.

00:20:20.720 --> 00:20:22.560
If you don't practice for years,

00:20:22.760 --> 00:20:24.360
you won't even make it to center stage.

00:20:25.200 --> 00:20:27.040
If you mess up one vocal run

00:20:27.600 --> 00:20:29.360
or if a spoken line lacks emotion,

00:20:29.640 --> 00:20:31.400
the whole opera is ruined.

00:20:34.320 --> 00:20:36.960
When others get off work,
you must practice.

00:20:38.040 --> 00:20:39.720
When they go on dates,

00:20:40.320 --> 00:20:41.440
you still have to practice.

00:20:42.200 --> 00:20:44.720
When they go shopping,

00:20:44.760 --> 00:20:46.840
watch a movie, or visit relatives,

00:20:47.320 --> 00:20:48.760
you're still stuck there practicing.

00:20:49.920 --> 00:20:51.200
From morning till night,

00:20:51.960 --> 00:20:55.400
only when you're washing up, eating,

00:20:56.520 --> 00:20:58.160
and sleeping do you stop practicing.

00:20:58.720 --> 00:21:00.600
You still have to keep it in mind

00:21:00.680 --> 00:21:02.240
and hum it under your breath.

00:21:02.560 --> 00:21:03.600
What's the point?

00:21:05.360 --> 00:21:07.520
Then why is everyone
fighting so hard for it?

00:21:09.360 --> 00:21:10.520
I don't know.

00:21:13.000 --> 00:21:14.000
Maybe they just like it.

00:21:16.280 --> 00:21:17.400
But different people

00:21:17.400 --> 00:21:19.200
like different things.

00:21:23.080 --> 00:21:24.840
But if I had to do it all over again,

00:21:25.560 --> 00:21:27.280
I'd still want to be the lead.

00:21:40.820 --> 00:21:46.260
(Qinchuan Province
Qinqiang Opera Theater)

00:21:47.760 --> 00:21:48.600
Master Chen.

00:21:52.760 --> 00:21:53.600
Chu Jiahe,

00:21:54.080 --> 00:21:55.680
your mom called you this morning.

00:21:55.760 --> 00:21:57.080
It sounded urgent.

00:21:59.520 --> 00:22:00.520
Thank you, Master Chen.

00:22:01.320 --> 00:22:03.280
Everyone used to fight for it.

00:22:04.120 --> 00:22:05.760
Now, everyone is turning it down.

00:22:06.920 --> 00:22:09.440
Is Li Hui Niang cursed or something?

00:22:12.960 --> 00:22:14.000
Stop pacing around.

00:22:14.000 --> 00:22:15.520
You're making me dizzy.

00:22:16.000 --> 00:22:16.840
Tell me.

00:22:17.000 --> 00:22:18.920
If we can't get Qin'e back,

00:22:19.520 --> 00:22:21.040
can we find someone to replace her?

00:22:21.520 --> 00:22:23.880
Who could? There's no one.

00:22:24.120 --> 00:22:26.120
We have to find a way. Think about it.

00:22:26.400 --> 00:22:28.760
This performance means everything.

00:22:28.760 --> 00:22:30.520
We can't afford a single mistake.

00:22:30.560 --> 00:22:32.520
I'd rather sacrifice myself

00:22:32.640 --> 00:22:34.360
than ruin the play.

00:22:34.840 --> 00:22:35.880
Gong Lili won't do.

00:22:37.200 --> 00:22:38.360
Shen Yun

00:22:38.720 --> 00:22:39.800
is too inexperienced.

00:22:40.600 --> 00:22:42.040
Chu Jiahe is an option.

00:22:42.800 --> 00:22:44.040
Her basics are decent.

00:22:44.760 --> 00:22:47.160
Her back injury
should be mostly healed now.

00:22:47.560 --> 00:22:49.120
You can just shorten the time

00:22:49.120 --> 00:22:50.160
for Woyu.

00:22:50.320 --> 00:22:52.120
She can do a bit of fire breathing.

00:22:52.320 --> 00:22:53.240
What do you think?

00:22:53.800 --> 00:22:55.160
Someone can sub for fire breathing

00:22:55.520 --> 00:22:56.880
and Woyu.

00:22:57.520 --> 00:22:59.040
But who can sub for Yi Qin'e?

00:22:59.880 --> 00:23:01.120
No one can replace her.

00:23:03.080 --> 00:23:04.800
With all these stand-ins,

00:23:04.880 --> 00:23:07.320
it'll ruin the provincial troupe's name.

00:23:08.360 --> 00:23:09.520
What do you suggest, then?

00:23:10.680 --> 00:23:11.520
I told you.

00:23:12.040 --> 00:23:13.000
Go ahead

00:23:13.520 --> 00:23:14.800
and sacrifice me.

00:23:15.240 --> 00:23:16.360
By your logic,

00:23:16.360 --> 00:23:17.560
this troupe is doomed.

00:23:17.560 --> 00:23:19.000
The provincial troupe is doomed.

00:23:19.320 --> 00:23:20.520
And you want to be an artist?

00:23:20.520 --> 00:23:22.200
What a joke.

00:23:22.720 --> 00:23:23.840
A joke of a troupe.

00:23:23.840 --> 00:23:25.120
A joke of an artist.

00:23:25.440 --> 00:23:26.280
Great.

00:23:37.160 --> 00:23:38.280
What do you want for dinner?

00:23:38.760 --> 00:23:40.520
I want ribbonfish.

00:23:40.840 --> 00:23:41.680
Ribbonfish.

00:23:42.720 --> 00:23:44.280
Braised or deep-fried?

00:23:44.680 --> 00:23:45.733
Deep-fried.

00:23:45.753 --> 00:23:46.399
Is that so?

00:23:46.920 --> 00:23:48.520
- Deep-fried ribbonfish then.
- Okay.

00:23:48.520 --> 00:23:49.680
Tell your uncle to buy it.

00:23:49.680 --> 00:23:51.400
You're not performing anyway.

00:23:51.520 --> 00:23:53.600
Eat whatever you want.
Gaining weight is fine.

00:23:53.600 --> 00:23:55.520
Why am I craving soy milk too?

00:23:56.240 --> 00:23:57.080
I'll go get you some.

00:23:57.940 --> 00:24:00.380
(Appliance repair)

00:24:04.800 --> 00:24:05.640
Qin'e.

00:24:05.840 --> 00:24:07.720
Go get some water. We're out.

00:24:07.960 --> 00:24:08.840
I'm washing veg.

00:24:18.920 --> 00:24:19.760
You'll quit?

00:24:22.440 --> 00:24:23.280
Jiahe,

00:24:24.760 --> 00:24:25.680
thank you.

00:24:26.280 --> 00:24:27.960
You were already gone when I woke up.

00:24:28.320 --> 00:24:29.160
I haven't even...

00:24:30.680 --> 00:24:31.520
Why?

00:24:33.400 --> 00:24:34.880
I haven't thought it through.

00:24:35.200 --> 00:24:36.320
It's as simple as that?

00:24:36.840 --> 00:24:37.720
And you're quitting?

00:24:39.560 --> 00:24:40.920
Why are you being so reckless?

00:24:42.400 --> 00:24:44.240
So many people worked so hard

00:24:44.640 --> 00:24:45.800
for that.

00:24:46.800 --> 00:24:47.680
And you got it.

00:24:48.800 --> 00:24:50.120
And this is how you treat it?

00:24:52.760 --> 00:24:54.520
The heavens gave you a gift.

00:24:56.760 --> 00:24:58.840
And you ruin others' livelihoods?

00:25:02.520 --> 00:25:04.320
If I had this chance, I...

00:25:10.880 --> 00:25:13.040
I should've let the fire burn you.

00:25:38.760 --> 00:26:03.840
(Qinqiang Opera Zha Mei An)
♪Wang Chao sends word; Ma Han reports♪

00:26:14.200 --> 00:26:15.720
Wonderful, just wonderful.

00:26:16.120 --> 00:26:16.960
How was it?

00:26:17.240 --> 00:26:18.360
I've still got it, right?

00:26:18.520 --> 00:26:19.560
Put some clothes on.

00:26:19.560 --> 00:26:20.640
Don't catch a cold.

00:26:21.120 --> 00:26:22.000
Here are the clothes.

00:26:24.680 --> 00:26:25.720
You play really well.

00:26:25.720 --> 00:26:27.080
You should play on stage.

00:26:27.600 --> 00:26:29.760
Going on stage isn't up to me.

00:26:30.400 --> 00:26:32.400
You have to adapt to the times,
you know?

00:26:33.720 --> 00:26:36.040
I don't even know
what times I'm in anymore.

00:26:37.160 --> 00:26:38.880
Do you remember
that when you were little,

00:26:40.120 --> 00:26:42.240
you hated singing opera

00:26:42.240 --> 00:26:43.720
and just wanted to go herd sheep?

00:26:46.080 --> 00:26:47.320
I can't go back.

00:26:48.360 --> 00:26:50.400
The sheep pen is too big for me

00:26:50.720 --> 00:26:51.920
to see the end now.

00:26:53.960 --> 00:26:55.160
You're still so young.

00:26:55.160 --> 00:26:56.560
Why so pessimistic?

00:26:57.200 --> 00:26:58.040
Look at me.

00:26:58.120 --> 00:26:59.240
At my age,

00:26:59.240 --> 00:27:00.720
I'm still trying to practice.

00:27:02.280 --> 00:27:04.160
Someone guided you when you were little

00:27:04.200 --> 00:27:05.240
and pushed you forward,

00:27:05.240 --> 00:27:06.280
but you wanted to rebel.

00:27:06.800 --> 00:27:08.520
You're free now.

00:27:09.040 --> 00:27:10.760
Your life is just beginning.

00:27:16.200 --> 00:27:17.400
I know you're in a tough spot.

00:27:17.560 --> 00:27:18.760
Let's do this. Here.

00:27:20.880 --> 00:27:22.440
Let's ask the heavens.

00:27:22.520 --> 00:27:23.360
Let's flip a coin.

00:27:23.680 --> 00:27:25.520
If it's heads, you stay.

00:27:25.520 --> 00:27:26.880
If it's tails, do as you please.

00:27:26.880 --> 00:27:27.720
How about that?

00:27:31.280 --> 00:27:32.800
I didn't do it on purpose.

00:27:34.280 --> 00:27:36.080
Can you see if it's heads or tails?

00:27:37.400 --> 00:27:39.560
Singing opera now is like herding sheep.

00:27:40.520 --> 00:27:42.720
I have to drive myself forward.

00:27:50.720 --> 00:27:51.960
Wait, let me pick it up.

00:27:54.160 --> 00:27:55.000
That's five cents.

00:27:57.000 --> 00:27:58.520
Say something.

00:27:58.520 --> 00:27:59.960
Don't just cry.

00:28:00.720 --> 00:28:02.520
Jiahe, Jiahe.

00:28:02.960 --> 00:28:03.840
What's wrong?

00:28:04.760 --> 00:28:05.680
Mom,

00:28:08.520 --> 00:28:09.520
I want to come home.

00:28:11.600 --> 00:28:12.440
Okay.

00:28:12.640 --> 00:28:13.880
Okay, don't panic.

00:28:13.880 --> 00:28:15.120
I'll pick you up tomorrow.

00:28:15.400 --> 00:28:18.080
Whatever it is, tell me at home.

00:28:19.520 --> 00:28:20.600
Jiahe.

00:28:21.200 --> 00:28:22.040
Jiahe.

00:28:25.220 --> 00:28:28.480
(Qinchuan Qinqiang Opera Theater)
♪Pei♪

00:28:29.270 --> 00:28:38.360
♪This flower is bright and pure♪

00:28:38.720 --> 00:28:41.280
(Yi Qin'e started singing opera again.)

00:28:41.680 --> 00:28:43.050
(Because aside from singing opera,)

00:28:43.160 --> 00:28:47.450
- ♪She's different♪
- (she was lost.)

00:28:47.450 --> 00:28:49.960
- ♪From peach blossoms♪
- (In life,)

00:28:49.960 --> 00:28:58.400
- ♪Peach blossoms fall in the wind♪
- (she needs a drive.)

00:29:03.660 --> 00:29:17.320
♪Red plum blossoms stand
in the wind and snow♪

00:29:17.320 --> 00:29:18.600
Would it kill you to slow down?

00:29:20.320 --> 00:29:21.160
Keep the rhythm.

00:29:27.880 --> 00:29:31.400
- ♪Thanks for the plum blossom♪
- Not powerful enough.

00:29:31.640 --> 00:29:32.960
Exactly. It's missing something.

00:29:33.150 --> 00:29:35.380
- ♪I bow to you♪
- That drum is weak, right?

00:29:35.380 --> 00:29:36.990
- ♪Thanks for your love♪
- Yeah.

00:29:38.360 --> 00:29:39.970
- ♪Don't let anyone♪
- Who are you?

00:29:40.090 --> 00:29:42.560
- ♪Touch this flower♪
- Someone should tell them.

00:29:42.560 --> 00:29:43.640
Right.

00:29:44.270 --> 00:29:46.620
- ♪Poetry♪
- Will you tell them?

00:29:46.760 --> 00:29:48.560
The food from our kitchen

00:29:48.560 --> 00:29:50.560
- is terrible now.
- Exactly.

00:29:50.560 --> 00:29:52.440
We can't even see a scrap of meat.

00:29:53.000 --> 00:29:55.360
- Right.
- If I managed the food here,

00:29:55.680 --> 00:29:57.520
I'd serve everyone Rou Jia Mo
for breakfast.

00:29:57.880 --> 00:29:59.320
Braised Pork for lunch.

00:29:59.640 --> 00:30:01.800
And for dinner, we'd have some

00:30:02.120 --> 00:30:02.960
stewed meat.

00:30:03.160 --> 00:30:04.160
Great, great.

00:30:04.240 --> 00:30:05.760
We'd eat our fill of meat.

00:30:05.760 --> 00:30:06.600
Right, right.

00:30:06.720 --> 00:30:08.680
Eating meat is good for the body.

00:30:08.680 --> 00:30:10.240
- Eating veggies every day
- Exactly.

00:30:10.320 --> 00:30:11.560
leaves us with no energy at all.

00:30:12.000 --> 00:30:13.160
Eating meat still...

00:30:16.560 --> 00:30:17.640
Isn't that...

00:30:18.320 --> 00:30:19.240
Well.

00:30:19.920 --> 00:30:21.040
Yi Qin'e's uncle!

00:30:21.440 --> 00:30:22.400
Good memory.

00:30:23.840 --> 00:30:25.640
Your niece is doing great now.

00:30:25.680 --> 00:30:28.560
She became the lead right after joining.

00:30:29.240 --> 00:30:30.560
Even if she is the lead,

00:30:30.600 --> 00:30:32.240
she still needs your drumming.

00:30:32.400 --> 00:30:33.560
That's for sure.

00:30:35.600 --> 00:30:37.840
Was that Zeng Mei just now?

00:30:38.560 --> 00:30:39.960
You surely know a lot.

00:30:41.200 --> 00:30:43.080
It felt a bit slow, didn't it?

00:30:44.440 --> 00:30:45.280
Slow?

00:30:46.400 --> 00:30:47.920
You have no clue.

00:30:48.600 --> 00:30:50.520
I can't explain it to an amateur.

00:30:50.800 --> 00:30:51.960
What is Zeng Mei?

00:30:52.600 --> 00:30:54.440
Zeng Mei is a boudoir scene.

00:30:54.680 --> 00:30:56.440
It has to be gentle and slow.

00:30:56.880 --> 00:30:58.160
Why play the drums so fast?

00:30:58.560 --> 00:31:00.080
So the lady and her maid can fight?

00:31:02.560 --> 00:31:05.120
But it still needs rhythm.

00:31:05.240 --> 00:31:06.520
Li Hui Niang's inner thoughts

00:31:06.520 --> 00:31:08.280
rely on your drum to build up.

00:31:08.440 --> 00:31:09.320
What do you mean?

00:31:11.040 --> 00:31:12.240
It feels a bit weak.

00:31:16.520 --> 00:31:17.600
Who said that?

00:31:17.960 --> 00:31:18.800
The audience.

00:31:19.200 --> 00:31:20.160
Which audience member?

00:31:23.360 --> 00:31:24.200
That skinny guy.

00:31:24.211 --> 00:31:25.244
And the ones next to him.

00:31:25.640 --> 00:31:27.320
Sparrow, Monkey.

00:31:28.120 --> 00:31:28.960
Come here.

00:31:32.200 --> 00:31:33.040
Lead drummer,

00:31:33.280 --> 00:31:34.200
what can we do for you?

00:31:34.760 --> 00:31:35.680
What's this about?

00:31:36.120 --> 00:31:37.920
You said my drumming is weak?

00:31:37.920 --> 00:31:39.720
What? We never said that.

00:31:39.720 --> 00:31:40.560
Absolutely not.

00:31:42.160 --> 00:31:43.080
He said it.

00:31:44.520 --> 00:31:46.680
How could you shift the blame onto us?

00:31:47.080 --> 00:31:48.093
Who are we to judge?

00:31:48.104 --> 00:31:49.690
How could we criticize the lead drummer?

00:31:49.840 --> 00:31:51.760
You said it's weak.

00:31:52.400 --> 00:31:53.600
I offered to tell him.

00:31:53.600 --> 00:31:54.800
And you two were thrilled.

00:31:55.120 --> 00:31:56.040
The box lunch.

00:31:56.200 --> 00:31:58.200
We meant the box lunch, right?

00:31:58.520 --> 00:31:59.360
Right.

00:31:59.680 --> 00:32:00.840
The lunch is too plain.

00:32:01.080 --> 00:32:02.320
Not even an egg in it.

00:32:02.760 --> 00:32:04.440
Lead drummer, we're heading out.

00:32:04.520 --> 00:32:05.360
They're serving food.

00:32:10.240 --> 00:32:11.240
I'll head out too then.

00:32:12.240 --> 00:32:13.080
Stop right there.

00:32:14.880 --> 00:32:16.440
What exactly do you do?

00:32:19.520 --> 00:32:21.000
Actually, I'm a drummer too.

00:32:21.040 --> 00:32:22.520
From Ningzhou County Troupe.

00:32:22.840 --> 00:32:25.120
I just wanted a quick chat with you.

00:32:26.440 --> 00:32:27.560
A pro?

00:32:27.880 --> 00:32:29.760
Let's chat. Come on, have a seat.

00:32:29.920 --> 00:32:31.360
Just sit on this stool.

00:32:34.520 --> 00:32:35.360
Tell me then.

00:32:35.760 --> 00:32:37.160
Where did my drumming lack energy?

00:32:38.680 --> 00:32:40.200
I'll try not to change it.

00:32:42.160 --> 00:32:44.240
I'll just speak my mind;
you just listen.

00:32:45.000 --> 00:32:46.520
As for the play Zeng Mei,

00:32:47.360 --> 00:32:49.520
the tempo and dynamics of the drumbeats

00:32:49.880 --> 00:32:50.840
must strictly follow

00:32:50.840 --> 00:32:53.240
the character's inner rhythm, right?

00:32:53.520 --> 00:32:54.560
Every single drumbeat

00:32:54.560 --> 00:32:56.520
must strike the actress to the core.

00:32:56.960 --> 00:32:59.040
It has to make her want to sing.

00:33:01.040 --> 00:33:02.160
The amateur has become

00:33:02.160 --> 00:33:03.000
a pro, huh?

00:33:03.880 --> 00:33:05.880
Are you lecturing me here?

00:33:06.853 --> 00:33:08.362
Can you play 5-beat Gong, 7-beat Gong,

00:33:08.373 --> 00:33:10.200
11-beat Gong, and 13-beat Cymbal?

00:33:10.313 --> 00:33:11.309
You don't have to say it.

00:33:11.320 --> 00:33:12.640
That's all wrong.

00:33:12.960 --> 00:33:14.120
I know

00:33:14.120 --> 00:33:15.280
about those terrible habits

00:33:15.280 --> 00:33:16.193
in your County Troupe.

00:33:16.320 --> 00:33:18.520
You don't even know
Double Drumsticks with Bangzi.

00:33:18.520 --> 00:33:19.600
With those tiny tricks,

00:33:19.600 --> 00:33:21.120
you think you're the expert here?

00:33:21.320 --> 00:33:22.640
This is the provincial troupe.

00:33:23.160 --> 00:33:24.720
Not your amateur local troupe.

00:33:24.720 --> 00:33:26.640
Don't bring your bad habits over here.

00:33:26.920 --> 00:33:28.800
We've got all sorts of people here.

00:33:28.960 --> 00:33:31.240
Novices trying to teach the masters.

00:33:32.080 --> 00:33:33.800
What is all this nonsense?

00:33:35.760 --> 00:33:38.520
If only you played drums

00:33:38.800 --> 00:33:39.840
as fast as you talk.

00:33:48.520 --> 00:33:49.600
OK, let me say a few words.

00:33:50.280 --> 00:33:51.120
In two days,

00:33:51.640 --> 00:33:53.280
we'll have our official performance.

00:33:53.640 --> 00:33:55.440
We've all worked so hard

00:33:55.440 --> 00:33:57.000
through so many days and nights.

00:33:57.000 --> 00:33:58.280
It's all for this very moment.

00:33:58.840 --> 00:34:01.600
Everyone performed very well today,

00:34:01.600 --> 00:34:02.680
including Shun.

00:34:03.440 --> 00:34:04.920
The lighting is pretty good today.

00:34:04.920 --> 00:34:06.240
It set the right atmosphere

00:34:06.240 --> 00:34:08.080
and kept the actors' expressions clear.

00:34:08.080 --> 00:34:08.920
Great job.

00:34:09.360 --> 00:34:10.600
You flatter me, Director.

00:34:10.640 --> 00:34:12.440
Our orchestra members...

00:34:14.080 --> 00:34:15.360
Our orchestra members,

00:34:15.360 --> 00:34:17.680
please take your instruments seriously.

00:34:18.000 --> 00:34:19.400
The drumsticks in your hands

00:34:19.400 --> 00:34:21.000
are the rhythm in the actors' hearts.

00:34:21.240 --> 00:34:23.280
- Stay focused!
- Yes!

00:34:23.280 --> 00:34:24.120
Good.

00:34:24.520 --> 00:34:25.400
Great work, everyone.

00:34:25.760 --> 00:34:27.240
Great work, Director.

00:34:33.520 --> 00:34:34.360
Qin'e.

00:34:34.670 --> 00:34:35.640
Director Feng.

00:34:35.640 --> 00:34:37.680
You look pretty tired today.

00:34:38.520 --> 00:34:40.360
I can't eat before fire breathing.

00:34:40.360 --> 00:34:42.120
I'll eat when I get back tonight.

00:34:42.280 --> 00:34:44.000
Make sure you get a good rest tonight.

00:34:44.160 --> 00:34:45.320
No need to come tomorrow.

00:34:45.400 --> 00:34:46.880
We're counting on you the day after.

00:34:47.200 --> 00:34:48.160
Got it, Director Feng.

00:34:52.840 --> 00:34:53.680
Hongbing is here.

00:34:54.240 --> 00:34:55.160
Hi, Hongbing.

00:34:55.280 --> 00:34:56.440
What's on the menu today?

00:34:56.440 --> 00:34:57.280
Anything for me?

00:34:58.000 --> 00:34:59.000
We had a deal, right?

00:34:59.280 --> 00:35:00.320
For a successful premiere,

00:35:00.520 --> 00:35:01.760
Weihua Barbecue

00:35:01.760 --> 00:35:02.600
for everyone!

00:35:02.600 --> 00:35:03.520
Really?

00:35:03.520 --> 00:35:05.080
You're so generous!

00:35:06.080 --> 00:35:06.920
Let's go, let's go!

00:35:07.680 --> 00:35:08.520
Hongbing.

00:35:14.680 --> 00:35:15.520
You didn't eat

00:35:15.520 --> 00:35:16.680
Pao Mo yesterday,

00:35:17.046 --> 00:35:18.320
so here's something light today.

00:35:18.320 --> 00:35:19.200
Qishan Saozi noodles.

00:35:19.320 --> 00:35:20.200
I can't eat.

00:35:20.720 --> 00:35:22.240
How about a banana then?

00:35:22.240 --> 00:35:23.120
They're nutritious.

00:35:23.120 --> 00:35:23.960
I don't want it.

00:35:25.880 --> 00:35:28.250
You haven't had a single sip of water.

00:35:28.250 --> 00:35:29.050
Let me change it.

00:35:29.061 --> 00:35:30.071
You've barely touched it.

00:35:30.082 --> 00:35:31.352
- You need to finish it.
- Stop.

00:35:31.363 --> 00:35:32.395
- Let me.
- Can you stop?

00:35:32.406 --> 00:35:33.673
I can't eat or drink anything.

00:35:35.520 --> 00:35:37.520
What's wrong? Did you throw up again?

00:35:40.166 --> 00:35:41.080
Take the afternoon off.

00:35:41.120 --> 00:35:42.000
Go see a doctor.

00:35:44.760 --> 00:35:45.600
Listen.

00:35:46.000 --> 00:35:47.560
Ever since the three-part coordination,

00:35:47.800 --> 00:35:49.720
you haven't been eating or drinking.

00:35:49.720 --> 00:35:50.720
This can't go on.

00:35:51.520 --> 00:35:52.600
You'll ruin your health.

00:35:52.600 --> 00:35:53.440
Do me a favor.

00:35:54.200 --> 00:35:55.040
What is it?

00:35:55.160 --> 00:35:56.280
Take your stuff.

00:36:28.840 --> 00:36:30.600
What kind of work do you even do?

00:36:30.600 --> 00:36:32.560
They say nothing
about you skipping work?

00:36:32.840 --> 00:36:34.040
What could they say?

00:36:34.560 --> 00:36:36.840
After Qin'e's three-part coordination,

00:36:36.840 --> 00:36:38.320
I took a long leave from work.

00:36:38.920 --> 00:36:41.040
We need to ensure the show
goes smoothly.

00:36:41.240 --> 00:36:43.520
Or Qin'e wouldn't even get
a sip of water.

00:36:43.520 --> 00:36:44.360
Poor thing.

00:36:45.000 --> 00:36:45.840
What about you?

00:36:47.920 --> 00:36:51.240
I'm also making sure the show goes well.

00:36:52.360 --> 00:36:54.080
Did you get kicked out?

00:36:57.120 --> 00:36:59.040
It's just tough love.

00:37:00.680 --> 00:37:01.520
Uncle.

00:37:01.720 --> 00:37:02.680
How are things with you?

00:37:03.600 --> 00:37:04.760
No love at all.

00:37:06.040 --> 00:37:06.880
What?

00:37:07.440 --> 00:37:08.960
My last trick didn't work?

00:37:09.680 --> 00:37:10.600
Your idea was garbage.

00:37:10.600 --> 00:37:12.200
Try a different approach.

00:37:12.720 --> 00:37:13.760
So what?

00:37:13.760 --> 00:37:15.600
Tactics are just superficial.

00:37:15.840 --> 00:37:16.680
In the end,

00:37:17.320 --> 00:37:19.360
it all comes down to a sincere heart.

00:37:21.260 --> 00:37:22.150
There are

00:37:22.520 --> 00:37:23.440
no tricks There are no tricks in love.

00:37:28.960 --> 00:37:30.680
But your eyes can't hide true love.

00:37:31.920 --> 00:37:32.760
Uncle,

00:37:33.160 --> 00:37:34.400
look into my eyes.

00:37:38.120 --> 00:37:39.000
I love you.

00:37:39.600 --> 00:37:40.440
Get lost.

00:37:40.800 --> 00:37:43.840
I turned down three 10-cent notes

00:37:43.840 --> 00:37:45.360
and a 50-cent note.

00:37:45.360 --> 00:37:48.560
I just wanted a 30-cent note.

00:37:49.520 --> 00:37:50.360
Isn't that weird?

00:37:51.520 --> 00:37:53.960
- You're back.
- What's making her laugh?

00:37:55.520 --> 00:37:57.600
The big star's uncle is back.

00:37:58.440 --> 00:37:59.400
You have no idea.

00:37:59.400 --> 00:38:01.520
It's all over Wenyi Road.

00:38:01.720 --> 00:38:03.960
The provincial troupe's Audrey Hepburn

00:38:04.360 --> 00:38:05.920
is none other than your Yi Qin'e.

00:38:06.840 --> 00:38:08.200
She's going on stage soon.

00:38:08.200 --> 00:38:09.960
I'll save you a ticket for the show.

00:38:10.640 --> 00:38:11.520
No way.

00:38:11.680 --> 00:38:13.440
I have to buy a ticket to support her.

00:38:14.320 --> 00:38:15.160
Caixiang,

00:38:15.520 --> 00:38:16.760
add a little more chili for me.

00:38:16.760 --> 00:38:17.600
Coming right up.

00:38:19.640 --> 00:38:21.040
Why change how you address her?

00:38:21.320 --> 00:38:22.600
No more "ma'am"?

00:38:22.600 --> 00:38:23.666
You're using her name now.

00:38:24.200 --> 00:38:26.080
We're not even family anyway.

00:38:26.120 --> 00:38:27.320
Why call me "ma'am"?

00:38:27.320 --> 00:38:28.160
Stop calling me that.

00:38:28.400 --> 00:38:30.360
See? Caixiang won't let me.

00:38:31.040 --> 00:38:31.920
Do you want a bowl?

00:38:31.920 --> 00:38:33.280
No, I have no appetite.

00:38:34.080 --> 00:38:34.920
What's wrong?

00:38:35.080 --> 00:38:36.120
Is it about the rehearsal?

00:38:38.040 --> 00:38:39.280
Qin'e is doing fine.

00:38:39.280 --> 00:38:40.800
Rehearsals are going smoothly.

00:38:41.680 --> 00:38:42.640
The lead drummer.

00:38:42.800 --> 00:38:44.560
The drumming wasn't energetic enough.

00:38:46.200 --> 00:38:47.360
What can we do?

00:38:48.040 --> 00:38:49.000
If the drums lack power,

00:38:49.000 --> 00:38:50.760
the whole show falls flat.

00:38:51.080 --> 00:38:51.920
Exactly.

00:38:52.800 --> 00:38:54.680
The lead drummer was right.

00:38:54.680 --> 00:38:55.520
It's just a job.

00:38:55.520 --> 00:38:57.000
They just show up to clock in,

00:38:57.000 --> 00:38:58.080
unlike us.

00:38:58.280 --> 00:38:59.680
We take the show seriously.

00:39:00.080 --> 00:39:02.280
If he hands me the drumsticks again

00:39:02.680 --> 00:39:03.840
and lets me play for Qin'e,

00:39:04.280 --> 00:39:05.560
the show will definitely succeed.

00:39:06.960 --> 00:39:08.920
But we don't get to make that call.

00:39:18.720 --> 00:39:19.600
Done with work?

00:39:21.120 --> 00:39:23.080
I figured it was about time
you got back.

00:39:23.080 --> 00:39:24.400
Quick, go wash your hands.

00:39:24.400 --> 00:39:25.240
I'm making noodles.

00:39:25.360 --> 00:39:27.760
Starting tomorrow,
you can stop helping out.

00:39:28.240 --> 00:39:29.680
Didn't we agree on this?

00:39:30.360 --> 00:39:31.520
Tomorrow is our last day.

00:39:31.520 --> 00:39:34.160
It's called finishing strong, you know?

00:39:35.106 --> 00:39:36.240
I'm not rehearsing tomorrow.

00:39:36.240 --> 00:39:37.593
Director Feng gave me the day off.

00:39:37.840 --> 00:39:38.680
That's perfect then.

00:39:38.960 --> 00:39:40.320
Let's go out and relax tomorrow.

00:39:40.680 --> 00:39:41.560
I'm not going.

00:39:44.080 --> 00:39:45.760
If you stay in your room tomorrow,

00:39:46.040 --> 00:39:48.640
you'll just overthink or practice,

00:39:48.640 --> 00:39:49.480
right?

00:39:50.320 --> 00:39:52.200
Then Director Feng giving you time off

00:39:52.200 --> 00:39:53.240
would be a total waste.

00:39:54.040 --> 00:39:54.880
I'll make the plans.

00:40:06.680 --> 00:40:07.520
Scar.

00:40:07.600 --> 00:40:08.440
Laohei.

00:40:08.600 --> 00:40:09.810
- Laohei
- Laohei.

00:40:12.640 --> 00:40:13.480
Six Bamboo.

00:40:14.280 --> 00:40:15.120
What's up?

00:40:15.120 --> 00:40:15.960
He's not paying.

00:40:16.560 --> 00:40:17.400
Seven Dot.

00:40:18.520 --> 00:40:19.600
- Two Bamboo.
- Won.

00:40:20.720 --> 00:40:21.600
I quit.

00:40:22.240 --> 00:40:23.080
I haven't won

00:40:23.080 --> 00:40:24.880
all day. What's the point?

00:40:24.880 --> 00:40:26.960
My luck is just terrible.

00:40:29.120 --> 00:40:29.960
Pay up.

00:40:30.720 --> 00:40:31.560
Bro.

00:40:31.760 --> 00:40:33.280
What are you doing?

00:40:33.520 --> 00:40:35.680
Would the Northwest Drum King owe you?

00:40:37.600 --> 00:40:39.400
Laohei, once I get paid,

00:40:39.400 --> 00:40:40.320
I'll pay up.

00:40:40.320 --> 00:40:41.520
Would I really owe them money?

00:40:41.880 --> 00:40:42.720
Right?

00:40:43.560 --> 00:40:44.400
No money?

00:40:46.800 --> 00:40:47.880
Money is tight.

00:40:49.040 --> 00:40:50.360
Go borrow some!

00:40:51.200 --> 00:40:52.280
Where would I borrow from?

00:40:52.280 --> 00:40:54.320
The whole troupe knows I play Mahjong.

00:40:54.440 --> 00:40:55.920
Who would lend me money?

00:40:56.640 --> 00:40:58.040
Then I can't help you.

00:40:58.600 --> 00:40:59.560
You guys figure it out.

00:40:59.800 --> 00:41:00.790
Wait.

00:41:03.160 --> 00:41:04.050
Stop! Stop!

00:41:04.070 --> 00:41:06.040
- Stop! Don't run!
- Help!

00:41:06.200 --> 00:41:08.020
- Stop! Stop!
- Murder!

00:41:08.040 --> 00:41:09.750
- Stop! Don't run!
- Murder!

00:41:09.800 --> 00:41:11.013
Stop! Stop!

00:41:11.080 --> 00:41:12.446
Stop!

00:41:12.570 --> 00:41:13.990
Stop! Stop!

00:41:14.090 --> 00:41:14.960
Stop!

00:41:16.340 --> 00:41:17.390
You ran, huh?

00:41:17.960 --> 00:41:19.120
What a wimp!

00:41:19.440 --> 00:41:20.280
Keep running!

00:41:29.840 --> 00:41:31.680
Who threw this banana peel?

00:41:33.680 --> 00:41:34.680
- Ouch!
- Let's go!

00:41:34.680 --> 00:41:35.840
- Du Ziteng!
- Slow down!

00:41:36.040 --> 00:41:37.560
Hold my foot!

00:41:37.920 --> 00:41:38.760
Du Ziteng!

00:41:39.240 --> 00:41:41.160
Check if this guy is faking it.

00:41:41.160 --> 00:41:42.000
Oh, my god, it hurts!

00:41:42.440 --> 00:41:43.680
- Sit.
- Bring him over here.

00:41:43.691 --> 00:41:44.640
- Easy.
- Put him here.

00:41:44.640 --> 00:41:45.480
What's going on here?

00:41:45.640 --> 00:41:46.480
Easy now.

00:41:48.040 --> 00:41:49.080
- Ouch!
- What happened?

00:41:49.080 --> 00:41:50.720
Sanyuan, see what's wrong.

00:41:51.160 --> 00:41:52.800
- Master Guo, what's wrong?
- Hu.

00:41:52.960 --> 00:41:54.840
Those young guys knocked me down.

00:41:55.320 --> 00:41:56.520
They broke my leg!

00:41:57.560 --> 00:41:58.400
Ow, ow, ow!

00:41:59.240 --> 00:42:00.280
I'm afraid it's broken.

00:42:01.280 --> 00:42:02.840
We need an X-ray at a big hospital.

00:42:03.280 --> 00:42:04.120
We can't delay.

00:42:04.360 --> 00:42:05.960
See? Look at what Hu said.

00:42:05.960 --> 00:42:06.800
Right.

00:42:06.880 --> 00:42:08.120
Carry him out, now!

00:42:08.120 --> 00:42:08.960
To the hospital.

00:42:09.000 --> 00:42:10.120
- Right.
- Easy, easy.

00:42:10.120 --> 00:42:11.240
Our troupe still has a show!

00:42:11.560 --> 00:42:12.880
How can I play the drums?

00:42:13.280 --> 00:42:14.760
You need to pay for my lost wages.

00:42:15.000 --> 00:42:15.840
What's going on?

00:42:16.600 --> 00:42:18.360
It's a minor thing. Let it go.

00:42:33.640 --> 00:42:34.480
Troupe Leader.

00:42:37.360 --> 00:42:38.200
Sanyuan.

00:42:38.560 --> 00:42:39.473
Perfect timing.

00:42:39.484 --> 00:42:40.550
I was just looking for you.

00:42:41.560 --> 00:42:42.813
Something's wrong in the troupe.

00:42:44.000 --> 00:42:45.940
- What?
- Come in.

00:42:48.400 --> 00:42:49.240
What's wrong?

00:42:49.760 --> 00:42:50.600
What do you need?

00:42:51.080 --> 00:42:52.000
Have a seat.

00:42:52.080 --> 00:42:53.200
Sit down, let me tell you.

00:42:55.360 --> 00:42:56.520
The troupe's lead drummer

00:42:57.640 --> 00:42:58.480
broke a bone.

00:42:59.160 --> 00:43:00.360
He really broke a bone?

00:43:01.360 --> 00:43:02.520
What? Did you know about this?

00:43:02.640 --> 00:43:03.600
No, I didn't.

00:43:05.020 --> 00:43:06.940
=The Lead=
(Preview)

00:43:09.040 --> 00:43:09.993
Sold out!

00:43:10.004 --> 00:43:10.930
- Any tickets?
- I'm...

00:43:10.930 --> 00:43:12.280
I'm the playwright for Yi Qin'e.

00:43:12.530 --> 00:43:14.160
(Sold out)
Right now, in Chang'an,

00:43:14.800 --> 00:43:16.920
besides trains to Guangdong
and Shenzhen,

00:43:17.000 --> 00:43:19.240
(You Xi Hu)
You Xi Hu tickets are the rarest.

00:43:19.520 --> 00:43:21.920
Isn't the troupe performing in Beijing?

00:43:21.920 --> 00:43:22.890
You're not allowed to go.

00:43:23.120 --> 00:43:24.440
If I don't go, what will you do?

00:43:24.640 --> 00:43:26.240
The audience sitting out there today

00:43:26.240 --> 00:43:27.880
is all from professional troupes.

00:43:27.880 --> 00:43:31.080
It won't be easy for Qin'e.

00:43:37.000 --> 00:43:41.620
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

00:43:43.090 --> 00:43:47.930
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

00:43:49.370 --> 00:43:53.560
♪We met and brushed past♪

00:43:55.120 --> 00:44:02.420
♪Your shadow drifted out of sight♪

00:44:16.790 --> 00:44:20.540
♪The stove fire blazed in my dream♪

00:44:22.140 --> 00:44:27.710
♪Lit up the tracks of pearly tears♪

00:44:28.830 --> 00:44:32.890
♪In my dream, water sleeves flew♪

00:44:34.020 --> 00:44:39.610
♪Hiding a lifetime of love♪

00:44:40.770 --> 00:44:44.970
♪The Qinling Mountains
crossed the stage♪

00:44:46.010 --> 00:44:51.640
♪Spring water brewed strong wine♪

00:44:52.810 --> 00:44:57.500
♪Sheep moved through the valley♪

00:44:58.180 --> 00:45:03.350
♪It felt like a promise
from another life♪

00:45:04.020 --> 00:45:09.050
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

00:45:10.080 --> 00:45:15.510
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

00:45:15.890 --> 00:45:21.170
♪If I chose again, I'd still roam♪

00:45:22.120 --> 00:45:27.930
♪All over this sunlit plateau♪

00:45:27.930 --> 00:45:33.350
♪The dream ends; the curtain falls♪

00:45:33.900 --> 00:45:39.410
♪Moonlight washes off this stage makeup♪

00:45:39.960 --> 00:45:44.920
♪The one in the mirror wears gray hair♪

00:45:45.940 --> 00:45:51.220
♪Already sang all my joy and sorrow♪

00:45:52.020 --> 00:46:01.050
♪Already shouted across Qinchuan Plain♪